## How To Get Started

### Prerequisites
1. Install [Node.js 18+](https://nodejs.org/)
2. Get a free [MongoDB Atlas](https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas) cluster
3. Get a free [OMDb API key](https://www.omdbapi.com/apikey.aspx)

### First-Time Setup
```bash
# 1. From the Filmcircle root directory:
npm run install:all

# 2. Copy env file and fill in your values
copy server\.env.example server\.env
# Edit server/.env with your MONGO_URI, JWT_SECRET, OMDB_API_KEY

# 3. Start the backend
npm run dev:server

# 4. In a separate terminal, start the frontend
npm run dev:client
```

Open **http://localhost:5173** in your browser.

### Running Tests
```bash
# Backend tests (Jest + Supertest + in-memory MongoDB)
npm run test:server

# Frontend tests (Vitest + React Testing Library)
npm run test:client

# Both
npm run test:all
```

---

## Edge Cases Covered

| Area | Edge Case | Response |
|---|---|---|
| Auth | Duplicate email | `409 Conflict` |
| Auth | Wrong password | `401 Unauthorized` |
| Auth | Expired token | `401`, prompt re-login |
| Auth | Missing field | `400` with field-level errors |
| Reviews | Duplicate review | `409` + reviewId for auto-update |
| Reviews | Invalid opinion value | `400 Bad Request` |
| Reviews | Empty movie search | Returns `{ results: [], total: 0 }` |
| Reviews | No reviews yet | Empty chart with CTA message |
| Clubs | Join already-joined | `409 Conflict` |
| Clubs | Leave not-a-member | `400 Bad Request` |
| Clubs | Post as non-member | `403 Forbidden` |
| Community | Delete other's post | `403 Forbidden` |
| Community | Empty post content | `400 Bad Request` |
| Community | Page beyond data | Empty array, no crash |
| General | Unknown route | `404` JSON response |
| General | Malformed JSON | `400 Bad Request` |
| General | OMDb API down | Returns graceful error in UI |

---

## Tech Stack Summary

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | React 18 + Vite + React Router v6 |
| Charts | Chart.js + react-chartjs-2 (Doughnut) |
| HTTP Client | Axios |
| Styling | Vanilla CSS with custom design tokens |
| Backend | Node.js + Express.js (MVC pattern) |
| Database | MongoDB + Mongoose |
| Auth | JWT + bcryptjs |
| Movie Data | OMDb API (IMDB-backed, free tier) |
| Frontend Tests | Vitest + React Testing Library |
| Backend Tests | Jest + Supertest + mongodb-memory-server |
| Hosting (Free) | Vercel (frontend) + Render (backend) + MongoDB Atlas M0 |

---

## Design Decisions

1. **Opinion-only reviews** (no star ratings) — as specified in synopsis
2. **OMDb proxy on backend** — API key never exposed to client bundle
3. **In-memory MongoDB for tests** — no real database touched during CI/CD
4. **Compound unique index** on [(movieId, userId)](file:///d:/College/Final%20project/Filmcircle/client/src/App.jsx#50-59) in Review — DB-level duplicate prevention
5. **Vite dev proxy** — no CORS config needed during development
6. **ReviewButtons auto-recovery** — on 409, automatically switches to update mode using the returned `reviewId`
